<div class="alert alert-info">
<p>
<%= icon('excalametion-triangle') %> 
The <i>name</i> of the package has to represents the package contents. 
In particular it has to obey the following rules: 
</p>
<ul>
  <li>lower case letters only</li>
  <li>. (dot), the - (minus sign), the + (plus sign) and numbers</li>
  <li>no spaces or special characters as accented letters, &, /, ?, ... </li> 
</ul>
<p>
Some examples of valid names for the Operating Systems course are: operatingsystems2012, operatingsystems, so-slide, so-exercise1, so+workers.
</p>
<p><%= icon('info-sign') %> The <i>description</i> of the package should be a self explanatory summary of the package contents.</p>
</div>
